conformance.naming

Class ListingTest

  • java.lang.Object
    • test.Test
      • conformance.naming.NamingTest
        • conformance.naming.ListingTest

  • public class ListingTest
extends NamingTest
    Test the naming server list and isDirectory methods.

    Items checked are:

    • list and isDirectory reject null pointer arguments.
    • list and isDirectory reject non-existent objects as arguments.
    • list rejects files as arguments.
    • The root directory is reported as a directory.
    • Diretories are listed correctly, and isDirectory returns the correct results for files and directories.

      • checkDirectoryListing

        private void checkDirectoryListing(Path path,
                         String[] expected_children,
                         boolean[] expected_kinds)
                            throws TestFailed
        Checks that directories are listed correctly, and checks that files and directories are distinguished correctly by isDirectory.
        Parameters:
        path - The directory to be listed.
        expected_children - The expected children of the directory.
        expected_kinds - An array of expected results of isDirectory calls. The calls will be made for each child of the directory, in the order they are given in expected_children.
        Throws:
        TestFailed - If the directory is not listed correctly, or if isDirectory misidentifies a directory or a file.
